Nigerian President Names World Bank Chief, Okonjo-Iweala, for His Cabinet

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-07-05T17:45:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-05/nigerian-president-names-world-bank-chief-okonjo-iweala-for-his-cabinet.html
Nigerian President  Goodluck Jonathan 
nominated Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala, a managing director at the  World
Bank , for a cabinet position, Senate President David Mark
announced today during proceedings in Abuja, the capital.  Okonjo-Iweala, who was  Nigeria ’s finance minister between
2003 and 2007, helped  Africa ’s top oil producer negotiate a $30
billion debt relief from Western creditors in 2005. She will be
screened by the Senate tomorrow, Mark said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net  